column1: 1. Children looked after continuously for at least 12 months as at 31 March  excluding those children in respite care. Only children who have been matched to key stage 2 data are included.
2. Figures for 2014 are based on provisional attainment data. Figures for all other years are based on final data.

3. This is the percentage of children looked after continuously for 12 months at 31 March aged 10 at the start of the academic year who had a valid Unique Pupil Number (UPN) recorded in the SSDA903 return.

4. This is the number of children eligible for key stage 2 assessments. Participation by independent schools is voluntary and therefore only includes results from those independent schools who  made a return and which met the statutory standards for assessment and moderation.
5. The state-funded school participation rate in 2010 was 74% due to industrial action. Local authority data for 2010 excludes missing records, for all other years they are included.
6. This is the expected level for the age group.
7. For 2012 and 2013, the assessment of writing was based on teacher assessments. Prior to 2012, the assessment of writing was based on test results and therefore earlier years are not comparable.
8. The grammar, punctuation and spelling test was introduced in 2013.
9. England totals exclude records with 'missing' (M) and 'pending maladministration' (P). Local authority data includes these (with the exception of 2010- see note 6).
Figures for previous years may be different to previously published figures as LAs may update information for past years.
National and Regional figures have been rounded to the nearest 10. Local Authority figures have been rounded to the nearest 5.
x = number less than or equal to 5 or percentage where the numerator is less than or equal to 5 or the denominator is less than or equal to 10.
See technical notes 19 and 20 for more information on rounding conventions.
